TY  - JOUR
AU  - Srinagesh, Padmanabhan
T1  - Nonlinear Prices and the Regulated Firm*
PY  - 1986
Y1  - 1986/02/01
DO  - 10.2307/1884641
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 101
IS  - 1
SP  - 51
EP  - 68
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper examines the problem of a regulated utility that sells output according to a nonlinear price schedule. Three results are obtained. First, rate-of-return regulation lowers the price schedule charged by the firm along its entire length. Second, some units of output will always be sold at a marginal price below true marginal cost. Third, a move from linear to nonlinear prices at a given fair rate-of-return can lead to an unambiguous increase in welfare.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1884641
ER  - 



